* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/æb.səˈljuː.ʃn̩/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/ˌæb.səˈl(j)u.ʃn̩/}}
* {{rhymes|en|uːʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|ecclesiastical}} An absolving of sins from ecclesiastical [[penalty|penalties]] by an authority. {{defdate|First attested around 1150 to 1350.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=9}}</ref>
# Forgiveness of sins, in a general sense. {{defdate|First attested around 1150 to 1350.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# The form of words by which a penitent is [[absolved]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{rfquotek|en|Shipley}}
# An [[absolve|absolving]], or setting free from guilt, sin, or penalty; [[forgiven]]ess of an offense. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: ''Government ... granting '''absolution''' to the nation.''
# {{lb|en|civil|_|legal|obsolete}} An [[acquittal]], or sentence of a judge [[declare|declaring]] an accused person [[innocent]]. {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} Delivery, in speech.
#: {{rfquotek|en|Ben Jonson}}

